args: I'm here, Grace. Now will you please tell\nme why you wanted to meet with me in\nthe dead of night?
I need to speak with you about the ideals\nheld by my former husband and myself.

My husband and I were researching ways
fusion magic could be used for medicinal
purposes. We hoped it might help those
who had lost limbs due to war or illness.

And we turned a blind eye to the inhumane
actions of the Syndicate, believing that the
lives saved through our research would
make up for any evil otherwise committed.
But we were wrong. A life lost can never\nbe regained, and the tragedies brought\nabout by our research cannot be undone.
What are you trying to say?
You said you were here because you\nagreed with the ideals of the Syndicate.

But I don'tâ€”not after what my husband
and I did to those people. We stole them
from their homes, placed them in chains...
We took EVERYTHING from them.
My only purpose in life now is to atone\nfor the sins of my past.
Look, if this is your roundabout way of\nrejecting me, that's fine.
But you make it sound like you want to\nbetray the Syndicate itself!
There was one other reason why I called\nyou out here, Barth. I need toâ€”
Enemy incoming! Enemy incoming!\nAll soldiers, prepare to intercept!
Get ready, chumps, because the Renegade\nQueen is here to WRECK YOU! WOOOOOO!
That is the subject Bauer permitted to\nescape! If we capture her, he will finally\nbe put in his place!
Gather everyone able to bear arms and\nconverge on her! I will not permit that\nwoman to slip our net a second time!
The raiders out there are apparently\nformer Syndicate test subjects, which\nmeans they're a tough lot for sure.
Eh, we're just guarding the test subjects,\nso it's not like it makes anyâ€”URK!
I'm gonna open your cell now, 'kay?
Are you here to save us?
Yes indeed! Now retreat with us back\nto the Halidom! RETREEEEEAT!
What are you doing, Grace?!\nYou can't free these subjects!
Besides, even if you do, the soldiers\nposted outside the base are sure to\nnotice a group of this size!
Not if there's an escape route they don't\nknow about.
Our decoy will draw the attention of the\nsoldiers outside while our friends slip in\nand seize control of the base.
From there, they'll free the captives and\nlead them to the escape route.
And you brought me here to silence me.\nIs that it?
It must be. After all, I'm the only other\nperson who knows about that path.
It's true that I could buy us a tremendous\namount of time by silencing you...
But I know the real you understands this:\nNo matter what ideals the Syndicate may\nespouse, their methods are unacceptable.
So come with me. Let's escape together.
There's only one me.\nThe one you see right before you.
And thus I would instead ask of you,\nwill you not reconsider your path?
It seems we're at an impasse.\nAnd there's no time... I'm sorry, Barth.
They're supposed to be right around...\nAh, there you are!
What can I say? Got carried away kicking\nsome Syndicate butt. How's everyone else?
Alain is guiding the people we saved back\nto the Halidom, and Grace...
Want me to set him down here?
Please. When that's done, can you help\nVida escort the captives out?
Grace? Please tell me you didn't knock\nlover boy out and drag him along with us.
You said you'd persuade him, not clock\nhim on the head until little birdies flew\nout of it going cheep cheep cheep!
He was not prepared to leave the\nSyndicate, so force was my only option.
Then that means he's a THREAT, Grace.\nSo again, why the hell is he here?
Because it was the right thing to do.\nThis man was subjected to experiments\njust as you were.
I found documents describing the\nexperiments performed by the Doctor\nwhile he was still alive.

One was called ï¼‚Magical Fusion
Duplication,ï¼‚ the goal of which was to
create copies of key Syndicate leadership
in the event of their deaths.
The Doctor would take a piece of the dead\nand combine it with a portion of a fiend\npossessing regenerative properties.

The subject born from that experimentâ€”
re-241â€”had the same appearance and
intellect as the deceased man they used
to create him.

Once the process was complete, the
Syndicate made him a researcher in order
to learn if the man's mind was as good of
a match as the body.
Okay, hang on. So you mean...
That man became Researcher 241,\nthe person who now lies before you.
And the body used to create him...\nwas my husband.
